<!-- /sections/banner-slider.liquid -->

{%- comment -%}
  Surgical LCP optimization: preload the first slide's hero image and
  load it eagerly + fetchpriority=high. All other slides keep the
  original lazysizes pattern. No CSS changes, no layout changes — the
  hero looks identical to the previous live behavior, but starts
  fetching the LCP image during HTML parse instead of waiting for
  lazysizes to detect intersection.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- comment -%}
  Single preload for the mobile hero only. Earlier we had two preloads
  (desktop + mobile) with media-query gating, but Chrome ignores the
  `media` attribute on <link rel="preload"> and fetches both regardless,
  wasting ~80KB on mobile pageloads (the unused desktop variant). Mobile
  is where LCP hurts most, so we preload mobile and let the desktop
  hero rely on its eager + fetchpriority="high" <img> attribute (which
  is fast enough on desktop where LCP isn't as cellular-bound).
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- comment -%}
  Body-side preload — fallback for non-homepage templates where this section
  is embedded (e.g. brand collection pages). On the homepage the <head>
  preload in layout/theme.liquid fires earlier and takes priority; this
  preload is then a harmless duplicate (Chrome deduplicates by URL).

  URL: image_url with format:'webp' to match the <source type="image/webp">
  srcset Chrome picks. Previously used img_url:'x502' (JPEG), causing a
  URL mismatch — Chrome preloaded JPEG but fetched WebP separately, wasting
  the preload entirely and adding ~2,581ms to resource_load_delay.
  type="image/webp" tells non-WebP browsers to skip this preload gracefully.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- comment -%}
  Body-side preload with imagesrcset (k83y, 2026-05-21). Matches the
  responsive mobile <source srcset> below (390w, 552w, 780w). On the
  homepage a head preload fires earlier (layout/theme.liquid, gated on
  template == 'index'). On non-homepage templates (brand collection
  pages, etc.) this body preload is the only one. Chrome deduplicates
  on URL so if both fire for the same size, only one fetch occurs.
  Removed single-URL pattern; added imagesrcset so 2x/3x-DPR phones
  download the correctly-sized variant rather than always 552px.
  NOTE: keep the three breakpoints (390, 552, 780) in sync with the
  <source> srcset below and with theme.liquid's head preload.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if section.blocks.size > 0 -%}
  {%- assign first_block = section.blocks.first -%}
  {%- if first_block.settings.slide_image_mobile -%}
    {%- assign _lcp_m = first_block.settings.slide_image_mobile -%}
    <link rel="preload" as="image" fetchpriority="high"
          href="{{ _lcp_m | image_url: width: 552, format: 'webp' }}"
          imagesrcset="{{ _lcp_m | image_url: width: 390, format: 'webp' }} 390w, {{ _lcp_m | image_url: width: 552, format: 'webp' }} 552w, {{ _lcp_m | image_url: width: 780, format: 'webp' }} 780w"
          imagesizes="100vw"
          type="image/webp">
  {%- endif -%}
  {%- if first_block.settings.slide_image_desktop -%}
    {%- assign _lcp_d = first_block.settings.slide_image_desktop -%}
  {%- endif -%}
  {%- comment -%}
    d6se 2026-05-21: Reserve the swiper's intrinsic height via aspect-ratio so the
    hero image can paint without waiting for Swiper JS (which initialises on
    DOMContentLoaded — late on this theme due to heavy JS, ~970ms after FCP in lab).
    Media-query gated: mobile uses the mobile image AR, desktop uses the desktop
    image AR. Section-scoped class so multiple banner sliders don't collide.
    Once Swiper inits it sets explicit inline pixel heights on slides; aspect-ratio
    on the swiper container remains as a hint but is overridden by the resolved
    flex layout. No post-init visual change when AR matches the image.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- if _lcp_m or _lcp_d -%}
    <style>
      {%- if _lcp_m %}.banner-slider-{{ section.id }} { aspect-ratio: {{ _lcp_m.width }}/{{ _lcp_m.height }}; }{% endif %}
      {%- if _lcp_d %}@media (min-width: 1009px) { .banner-slider-{{ section.id }} { aspect-ratio: {{ _lcp_d.width }}/{{ _lcp_d.height }}; } }{% endif %}
    </style>
  {%- endif -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- comment -%}
  J11 S21 (bd 2i8b.75, 2026-06-11): full-bleed banner on mobile — confirmed by
  the web team on BOTH the P8 preview and the LIVE P6 site, so the fix ships in
  the section itself (shared by both themes) rather than css-overrides (whose
  P8 state must not reach live). `.banner-slider .wrapper` is (0,2,0) — beats
  the stock `.wrapper` padding regardless of stylesheet order, and needs no
  helper class. Inline <style> may repeat if the section renders twice on a
  page; the CSS is idempotent.
{%- endcomment -%}
<style>
  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .banner-slider .wrapper {
      padding-left: 0;
      padding-right: 0;
      max-width: none;
      margin: 0;
    }
    .banner-slider .swiper {
      width: 100%;
    }
    /* J16 S14 (bd 2i8b.78): belt-and-suspenders for the recurring "still gapped"
       report. The wrapper rule above already makes the banner full-bleed (proven:
       applying it jumps the wrapper to viewport width, and the image fills its
       slide). This block additionally forces the slide's content chain to fill,
       eliminating any mobile-only flex-shrink edge case where the centred <a>/
       <picture> could sit narrower than the slide. Strictly improves toward
       full-bleed — never regresses (an already-filling image stays filling). */
    .banner-slider .swiper-slide {
      display: block;
    }
    .banner-slider .swiper-slide > a,
    .banner-slider .swiper-slide picture {
      display: block;
      width: 100%;
    }
  }
</style>
<div class="wrapper banner-slider-wrapper">
  <div class="swiper banner-slider-{{ section.id }}" data-slide-delay="{{section.settings.slide_delay}}">
    <!-- Additional required wrapper -->
    <div class="swiper-wrapper">
      <!-- Slides -->
      {% for block in section.blocks limit: section.blocks.size %}
        <div class="swiper-slide" data-swiper-autoplay="{{section.settings.slide_delay}}">
          {%- comment -%}
            First slide: eager + fetchpriority=high (LCP element).
            Other slides: native browser lazy loading. Removed legacy
            lazysizes pattern (`class="lazyload"` + `data-src`) — that
            required JS hydration before the img had any src to load
            from, delaying off-screen slides longer than necessary.
            Native `loading="lazy"` on a plain `src` lets the browser
            decide intersection without a JS roundtrip.
          {%- endcomment -%}
          {%- if forloop.first -%}
            {%- assign img_loading = 'eager' -%}
          {%- else -%}
            {%- assign img_loading = 'lazy' -%}
          {%- endif -%}
          {%- comment -%}
            <picture> + <source> swap so mobile only downloads the
            mobile image (was both, hidden via display:none — wasted
            ~80KB on every mobile pageload). Mobile breakpoint matches
            the hidden-lap-and-up class boundary at 1009px so the
            picked source aligns with what's actually rendered.
          {%- endcomment -%}
          {%- comment -%}
            WebP rollout 2026-04-29 (Task 5 batch — re-attempt after
            2026-04-27 revert). Earlier attempt silently dropped the
            <source type="image/webp"> line. Re-trying with the exact
            same pattern proven on product-grid-item-branded.liquid +
            image-fill.liquid: pass the raw image_picker setting (NOT
            .src) into image_url with width + format params. Pipeline
            6.1.3 image_picker IS an Image object per Shopify docs —
            previous failure may have been syntax-related or rendered
            from a stale cache. Smoke-test will verify the
            type="image/webp" line survives in the rendered HTML; if
            it doesn't, revert this hunk and re-park.

            Banner is the LCP element on homepage — successful WebP
            here saves ~30–50% on the highest-impact image of the
            page. Mobile slide is ~250 KB JPEG, desktop ~150 KB JPEG;
            WebP variants would be ~125 KB and ~75 KB respectively.
          {%- endcomment -%}
          {%- assign _img_d = block.settings.slide_image_desktop -%}
          {%- assign _img_m = block.settings.slide_image_mobile -%}
          {% if block.settings.slide_image_url != blank %}
            <a href="{{block.settings.slide_image_url}}">
              <picture>
                {% if _img_d %}<source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 1009px)" srcset="{{ _img_d | image_url: width: 1400, format: 'webp' }}">{% endif %}
                {% if _img_m %}<source type="image/webp" srcset="{{ _img_m | image_url: width: 390, format: 'webp' }} 390w, {{ _img_m | image_url: width: 552, format: 'webp' }} 552w, {{ _img_m | image_url: width: 780, format: 'webp' }} 780w" sizes="100vw">{% endif %}
                <source media="(min-width: 1009px)" srcset="{{ _img_d | image_url: height: 788 }}">
                <img class="banner-slide-img" src="{{ _img_m | image_url: height: 502 }}" alt="Banner Slide 1" width="{{ _img_m.width | default: _img_d.width | default: 552 }}" height="{{ _img_m.height | default: _img_d.height | default: 502 }}" loading="{{ img_loading }}"{% if forloop.first %} fetchpriority="high"{% endif %}>
              </picture>
            </a>
          {%- else -%}
            <picture>
              {% if _img_d %}<source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 1009px)" srcset="{{ _img_d | image_url: width: 1400, format: 'webp' }}">{% endif %}
              {% if _img_m %}<source type="image/webp" srcset="{{ _img_m | image_url: width: 390, format: 'webp' }} 390w, {{ _img_m | image_url: width: 552, format: 'webp' }} 552w, {{ _img_m | image_url: width: 780, format: 'webp' }} 780w" sizes="100vw">{% endif %}
              <source media="(min-width: 1009px)" srcset="{{ _img_d | image_url: height: 788 }}">
              <img class="banner-slide-img" src="{{ _img_m | image_url: height: 502 }}" alt="Banner Slide 1" width="{{ _img_m.width | default: _img_d.width | default: 552 }}" height="{{ _img_m.height | default: _img_d.height | default: 502 }}" loading="{{ img_loading }}"{% if forloop.first %} fetchpriority="high"{% endif %}>
            </picture>
          {% endif %}

        </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    <!-- If we need pagination -->
    <div class="swiper-pagination"></div>
    <div class="swiper-button-next"></div>
    <div class="swiper-button-prev"></div>
  </div>
</div>

{%- comment -%}
  Vertex home_below_hero slot is now wired via templates/index.json
  ("vertex_home_recs" section using sections/vertex-recommendations.liquid).
  No embedded render here — the standalone section keeps placement
  configurable from the theme editor.
{%- endcomment -%}

{% schema %}
  {
    "name": "Banner Slider",
    "class": "banner-slider",
    "max_blocks": 10,
    "settings": [
      {
        "type": "checkbox",
        "id": "enable_section",
        "label": "Enable Section",
        "default": false
      }, {
        "type": "range",
        "id": "section_margin_top",
        "min": 0,
        "max": 100,
        "step": 1,
        "label": "Section margin top",
        "default": 20
      }, {
        "type": "range",
        "id": "section_margin_bottom",
        "min": 0,
        "max": 100,
        "step": 1,
        "label": "Section margin bottom",
        "default": 20
      }, {
        "type": "range",
        "id": "slide_delay",
        "min": 1000,
        "max": 5000,
        "step": 1000,
        "label": "Slide delay",
        "info": "Slide delay uses milliseconds, so 1 second is equal to 1000",
        "default": 3000
      }
    ],
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "banner_slide",
        "name": "Banner Slide",
        "settings": [
          {
            "type": "image_picker",
            "id": "slide_image_desktop",
            "label": "Banner Slide Image (Desktop)",
            "info": "1400px width x 788px height recommended"
          }, {
            "type": "image_picker",
            "id": "slide_image_mobile",
            "label": "Banner Slide Image (Mobile)",
            "info": "552px width x 502px height recommended"
          }, {
            "type": "url",
            "id": "slide_image_url",
            "label": "Banner Slide URL"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "presets": [
      {
        "name": "Banner Slider",
        "category": "Sliders",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "banner_slide"
          }, {
            "type": "banner_slide"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
{% endschema %}
